commit.message:
Better logic for enabling the vector extensions

The extension must be defined (this is determined by the `configure`
script), and it must not be disabled (this is done by the user on the
command line using e.g. `--disable-avx`).

commit.message: Fixed issue with checkpointing when root age is calibrated; clock rate and root age now checked against each other just before the chain starts.
updated NEWS
minor check

refactored fbd prior calculation

also added support for the lambda,mu,psi parameterization (exp priors for these 3 rates, considered as a hidden feature for now)

also more tolerance on checking fixed clock tree and rate

the rest is just about formatting
updated help messages for fbd related parameters
fixed setting popsizepr and growthpr for protein data

a few more fixes, which are:

1. more informative headers (lnPrior, lnLike)
2. fixed sigma (sd_log) in lnorm rate variation across sites
3. fixed calculating restriction data when beagle is enabled
silenced several compiler warnings
brought the changes and fixes from a local branch
extended the coalescent prior to support serially-sampled tips (#270)
